			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">thefox wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Can you explain to me why you call the filter [0.5 0.5 0], isn't [0.5 0.5] equivalent?</div><br />I assume the phase shift is easier to see if the filter has an odd number of taps.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">it says &quot;PAL alternates the broadcast sign of the V component, so on PAL every odd scanline will use the appropriate opposite phase—e.g. phases 5-C are respectively replaced with C-5.&quot;, why not 5-B and B-5?</div><br />The PPU outputs hues in units of 30 degrees. Neither 135 nor 225, the standard phase values for PAL colorburst, is a multiple of 30. First I'll need to see on a scope what the 2C07 is actually outputting for the colorburst and for the picture proper.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

